  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. Under sentencing guidelines for white-collar crimes of this magnitude, a lengthy prison sentence is disproportionate, while the outburst from the spectator is legally irrelevant to the sentencing calculation. Taking into account the breach of trust and the remaining financial loss, a period of six months is sufficient to serve as a punitive measure and a deterrent without causing irreparable harm to a first-time offender's rehabilitation prospects.",
  "verdict": 6
